==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gumbo
<hw>Gum"bo</hw> <pr>(g⟦ucr⟧m"b⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Written
also <ets>gombo</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A soup thickened with the
mucilaginous pods of the okra; okra soup.</def>
<specif>Especially,</specif> <def>A thick stew made with chicken
(<stype>chicken gumbo</stype>), or seafood (<stype>seafood
gumbo</stype>), thickened with okra or file, and also containing greens
and often hot spices; it is particularly popular in Louisiana.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The okra plant or its pods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gumboil</ent>⟦br⟧
